frameDefinitions: This frame is concerned with Cognizers remembering and forgetting mental Content.
An Employer hires an Employee, promising the Employee a certain Compensation in exchange for the performance of a job.
A Cognizer applies oneself to commit a Pattern to memory, so that the Cognizer would recognize future examples of the Pattern or be able to reproduce it.
An Agent changes a Patient's ability to resist literal or figurative attack.
In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. '' 'In her heart she must retain bitterness against those who had killed him.'
In this frame, a Booker brings about a situation where an Organization plans to provide Services to a Client at a particular Scheduled_time.
frameExamples: John was <t>hired</t> to clean up the file system.
A gaggle of students were frantically <t>memorizing</t> the answers out in the hall.
We <t>bulwarked</t> the castle against the oncoming horde.
In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
We can <t>book</t> you a boatride on the Somme or a special tour of the Louvre .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the person whose mental <fen>Content</fen> is at issue.
The <fen>Content</fen> is the mental content that a <fen>Cognizer</fen> retains or forgets.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject the <fen>Cognizer</fen> mental <fen>Content</fen> is about.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the remembering or forgetting of mental <fen>Content</fen> occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the remembering or forgetting takes place.
The person whom the <fen>Employer</fen> takes on as an <fen>Employee</fen>, obligating them to perform some <fen>Task</fen> in order to receive <fen>Compensation</fen>.
The person (or institution) that takes on an <fen>Employee</fen>, giving them  <fen>Compensation</fen> in return for the performance of an assigned <fen>Task</fen>.
The action that the <fen>Employee</fen> is taken on by the <fen>Employer</fen> to do.
The label given to a particular type of employment.
The <fen>Field</fen> that the <fen>Employee</fen> is going to work in for their <fen>Employer</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when an <fen>Employer</fen> hires the <fen>Employee</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Employer</fen> hires the <fen>Employee</fen>.
The sentient being that focuses on a <fen>Pattern</fen> so that it will remain in the memory.
The phenomenon that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> observes and commits to memory.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
The location wherein the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> makes the <fen>Patient</fen> more resistant to attack.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that is being made more resistant.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> makes the <fen>Patient</fen> more resistant.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> makes the <fen>Patient</fen> more resistant.
The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity that is intended to receive the <fen>Services</fen> of the <fen>Organization</fen>.
The goods or labor that the <fen>Client</fen> requests the <fen>Organization</fen> preserve for future consumption or rendering.
The entity that enters into its records the request of the <fen>Client</fen> to retain <fen>Services</fen> in the future.
The future point in time when the <fen>Client</fen> arranges for the <fen>Organization</fen> to provide <fen>Services</fen>.
The entity that contacts the <fen>Organization</fen> directly.  In many if not most cases, a <fen>Booker</fen> is also a <fen>Client</fen>, but the roles may also be separated, e.g. a travel agent.
The time at which the reserving event takes place.
The location the <fen>Booker</fen> performs the action.
